A vintage 1950s-style illustration showing a massive conveyor belt snaking through a cross-section of the Earth, carrying colorful consumer goods—plastic toys, electronics, clothing, appliances—from a smoking factory on one end, through a stylized suburban home in the middle, and emptying into an overflowing landfill on the other end. The scene uses muted olive greens, burnt oranges, and faded yellows typical of mid-century educational posters. Small human figures stand dwarfed beneath the towering machinery and mountains of discarded objects. The composition reveals hidden underground pipes and toxic streams connecting each stage, while storm clouds gather overhead. The aesthetic evokes vintage infographic charts with a slightly ominous undertone.
